Correct — this fails **before `/sales-points`**.

From your log, the failure is in:

```text
AuthService.handleCallback(...)
AuthController.callback(...)
```

So the flow is:

```text
/auth/callback
  ↓
AuthService.handleCallback()
  ↓
partner-repository /users/another-test-user
  ↓
500 or user not found
  ↓
exception thrown
```

Because of that, the browser never reaches:

```text
GET /sales-points
```

So your `SalesPointController` failure page cannot handle this case.

You need a **global UI error handler** for auth/callback errors.

Add this:

```java
@ControllerAdvice
@Slf4j
public class UiExceptionHandler {

    @ExceptionHandler(Exception.class)
    public ModelAndView handleGenericUiException(Exception ex) {
        log.error("Unhandled UI error", ex);

        ModelAndView mv = new ModelAndView("views/ui-error");

        mv.addObject("pageTitle", "Erreur technique");
        mv.addObject("iconPath", "/images/icons/tools.svg");
        mv.addObject("title", "Oups, un problème<br>technique est survenu.");
        mv.addObject("message",
                "Nous n’avons pas pu charger les données nécessaires pour le moment.");
        mv.addObject("strongMessage",
                "Réessayez dans quelques minutes. Si le problème persiste, contactez votre Zone Manager pour obtenir de l’aide.");

        return mv;
    }
}
```

Then rename your reusable page to:

```text
templates/views/ui-error.html
```

and CSS:

```text
static/css/ui-error.css
```

Then it can be used by:

```text
AuthController
SalesPointController
any UI controller exception
```

For this exact case, also handle missing user inside `AuthService.handleCallback()`:

```java
try {
    User user = partnerRepositoryClient.getUserById(username);
} catch (Exception e) {
    throw new UiTechnicalException("Unable to load user from partner repository", e);
}
```

Then in the global handler:

```java
@ExceptionHandler(UiTechnicalException.class)
public ModelAndView handleUiTechnicalException(UiTechnicalException ex) {
    return technicalErrorView();
}
```

So yes: for errors before sales-point screen, use **global `@ControllerAdvice`**, not `SalesPointController`.
